title_full:
Nik Colk Void

              —
              Bucked Up Space
            
              (Editions Mego)
label: Editions Mego
description:
Nik Colk Void's debut solo album is a slippery blacklight synth diary of limber cold-wave muscle, improvised warehouse techno and grizzled neo-no-wave slop. RIYL Raime, Suicide, Not Waving, Chris and Cosey.

As a member of Factory Floor, Kaito, Carter Tutti Void (with Chris Carter and Cosey Fanni Tutti) and NVPR (with Peter Rehberg), Void has been... more

description:
Delightful jammer from the semi-mythical Swell Maps / Television Personalities-affiliated Scottish indie pop janglers The Catburgers. Essential listening for any C86 or Flying Nun aficionados - think The Pastels, The Field Mice, BMX Bandits.

label: Tresor Records
description:
Anime rave mashup queen Yazzus joins the Tresor stable with an Afro-futurist hybrid dance tome that feels like a necessary re-examination of electro. Highly recommended!

Born in Ghana, raised in London and now based in Berlin, Yazzus brings a confident spread of experience to her Tresor debut. She was a regular fixture on the London circuit before decamping... more

label: Schwyn
description:
If BoC did dembow, it would surely sound like DJ Python’s revival of his Luis moniker for AD 93, an unmissable love note to deep reggaeton and ‘90s electronica.

Last heard under this name in 2016 for 1080p, Python’s Luis moniker is where his passions for the melancholy of BoC, Æ, and AFX most explicitly meet his heritage. Puckered melodies elide with... more
